# ModLoader Installer Walkthrough (Fabric)

## Changes
- **New Service**: [ModLoaderService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModLoaderService.cs)
    - Implemented [InstallFabricAsync](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModLoaderService.cs#22-84) to fetch Fabric metadata from `meta.fabricmc.net`.
    - Downloads all required libraries to `.minecraft/libraries`.
    - Returns the Fabric Profile JSON for further processing.
    - Uses [DownloadBatchAsync](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Network/DownloadService.cs#156-208) for efficient parallel downloading.
- **Integration**: [ModpackService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs)
    - Detected `fabric-loader` dependency in `.mrpack` metadata.
    - Calls `ModLoaderService.InstallFabricAsync` during import.
    - Uses the returned Fabric JSON as the base for the Modpack's version definition, ensuring the instance has the correct main class and libraries.

## Verification
- [x] **Code Compilation**: `dotnet build` successful.
- [x] **Logic Check**: 
    - [ModpackService](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs#12-271) correctly identifies Fabric.
    - [ModLoaderService](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModLoaderService.cs#17-21) fetches the correct JSON structure.
    - Libraries are added to the download queue.
    - JSON is saved with the correct ID.

